    "body": "I'm not familiar with the ionic framework but I assume you have standard contract files (*.sol)?\r\n\r\nInstall Truffle:\r\nsudo npm install -g truffle\r\n\r\nMake a directory for your DApp:\r\nmkdir ionic_new\r\ncd ionic_new\r\n\r\nCreate a new project:\r\ntruffle init\r\n\r\nCopy your contract .sol files into the contracts/ directory\r\n\r\nShould be able to compile your contracts now... truffle compile --all\r\n\r\nThe next parts you need to read up on as they are specific to your DApp...\r\n\r\n1. Create a migration file in the migrations directory.... like: 2_deploy_contracts.js\r\n2. Update the truffle-config.js and define your networks \r\n\r\nFire up TestRPC / Ganache and run: truffle migrate --reset   or    truffle test\r\n\r\nI recommend this link for finer details:\r\nhttps://truffleframework.com/docs/truffle/reference/configuration",
